                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12548474" author="jimk" created="Wed, 5 Dec 2007 00:12:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Absolutely correct.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While HTable is thread safe it is not multi-update friendly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What I would propose doing is allowing multiple concurrent updates and that the lockid be the identifier for a particular update.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12548476" author="bryanduxbury" created="Wed, 5 Dec 2007 00:21:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If we actually want to have the ability to have multiple updates in progress at once, why don&apos;t we expose the BatchUpdate object, or better, create some sort of Bigtable-esque RowMutation class that the users can create and then apply to a table? It&apos;d be nicer and more object-oriented than simply methods hanging off of HTable and grouped by a random number.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12548486" author="jimk" created="Wed, 5 Dec 2007 00:51:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually BatchUpdate is a public class right now, but we&apos;d have to make some changes to it and HTable to implement your suggestion. The changes to BatchUpdate would have to be such that it doesn&apos;t break the current HTable to region server wire protocol, but it is doable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding a new class would mean changing the wire protocol which would require an incompatible change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12548497" author="bryanduxbury" created="Wed, 5 Dec 2007 01:27:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If BatchUpdate has to be a certain way to maintain the wire protocol,  &lt;br/&gt;
that seems to me to be a respectable reason to make that class  &lt;br/&gt;
private and make a new public class that can be transformed into a  &lt;br/&gt;
BatchUpdate properly behind the scenes. The existing mutation methods  &lt;br/&gt;
could then be changed under the hood if we&apos;re determined to maintain  &lt;br/&gt;
the existing interface.&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
                            <comment id="12559156" author="jimk" created="Tue, 15 Jan 2008 18:12:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-35&quot; title=&quot;[hbase] Make BatchUpdate public in the API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-35&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-2611&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, this issue is redundant.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
